{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Jira reconciler correctness & the ticket-store corruption it caused\n\nBroadened from the original store-only charter (\"concurrency hardening + corruption\nremediation, follow-ups to f193\"). Root-cause work (bug saggy-pupil-plant / f193 and the\n2026-07-07 reconciler deep-dive, session log spirited-balsamic-sealion) established the\nthroughline: **the Jira reconciler is the epicenter**. Its 20-min CI pass is the most active\nconcurrent writer of the `tickets` branch, and its shallow-fetch + rebase workflow (RC1)\n*caused* the ~2,400-issue store corruption. This epic owns three coherent bands of work.\n\n## Context\n- **RC1 (fixed, #1):** reconciler CI used shallow `--depth=1` fetch + `git rebase`, resurrecting\n  compaction-deleted source files -> `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` (commit 5a7548a). Historical damage remains.\n- **RC2b (band A):** a concurrent write on a stale base gets an HLC below a peer's snapshot horizon;\n  a clean union-merge keeps it, but replay's positional skip drops it -> silent data loss.\n- **Invariant gap (band A):** docs I1 says compaction RENAMEs folded files to `*.retired`; the code hard-`os.remove()`s them.\n- **Convergence redesign (landed, epic file-lens-jewel; band B):** three-way-merge baseline + binding\n  lifecycle (ADRs 0026-0029, 0031) shipped, but the per-binding baseline runs dual-write SHADOW —\n  the Phase-3 consumer swap is not yet live.\n- **Latent reconciler gaps (band C):** silent same-field clobber with no conflict signal; hard-delete ->\n  re-create unreachable + false comment; silent field-allowlist drop; coarse bulk-path 429 handling.\n  Design as a whole matches/beats OSS + commercial-tier peers (see session log). Single-hop status\n  transitions are ACCEPTED / out of scope.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- **A. Store hardened + remediated:** compaction non-destructive (I1 `*.retired`); no concurrent\n  sub-horizon append silently dropped on replay (RC2b); live-store `rebar fsck` reports zero\n  SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT / ORPHAN_EVENT / MISSING_CREATE.\n- **B. Convergence fully live:** the per-binding baseline is the authoritative direction arbiter\n  (Phase-3 consumer swap flipped + validated on live passes).\n- **C. Latent gaps closed:** true both-sides field conflicts are recorded (not silently clobbered);\n  hard-delete -> re-create works end-to-end; outbound field-allowlist drops are observable; bulk-path\n  429 honors Retry-After.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Band A children landed: A1 (`*.retired`), A2 (RC2b horizon-safe), A3 (live-store remediation to zero fsck).\n- [ ] Band B: B1 (Phase-3 baseline consumer swap) parented + tracked (operator/live-ops owned).\n- [ ] Band C children landed: C1 (clobber conflict signal), C2 (hard-delete re-create), C3 (field-allowlist alert), C4 (bulk-path 429 parity).\n- [ ] Dependency edges wired: A1->A2, A1->A3, A2->A3; C1 relates_to B1.\n- [ ] Risk #5 (single-hop status transitions) explicitly accepted / out of scope.\n","title":"Jira reconciler correctness & the ticket-store corruption it caused — convergence completion, latent-gap closure, and store hardening + remediation (f193 follow-ups)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783470404895330001,"uuid":"2386b059-a348-4bbe-a394-c0d0d181a14a"}